# Zinc Project Conventions

## Python

- Format with `ruff format`, lint with `ruff check --fix`.
- All public symbols must have type annotations and Google-style docstrings.
- Logger: `import structlog; log = structlog.get_logger()` — never `print()`.
- Secrets from environment variables only — never hardcoded.
- Pydantic v2 for all data models.

## C++

- Standard: C++20. Formatter: `clang-format` (config at repo root).
- Each `.cpp` includes its own header first.
- Prefer `std::span`/`std::string_view` over raw pointers in APIs.

## SQL

- All SQL linted with `sqlfluff --dialect postgres`.
- Migrations are reversible Alembic scripts in `services/<svc>/migrations/`.

## Tests

- New behaviour → new test in `tests/unit/` or `tests/smoke/`.
- Smoke tests require `@pytest.mark.smoke` and depend on running infra.

## Commits

- Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` (Conventional Commits).
- Types: feat, fix, chore, docs, test, refactor, perf, ci.
- No secrets in commit messages.

